content: I don't have personal beliefs, but i can provide an informed answer. the comparison of modern electronic music with beethoven's compositions is subjective, and it depends on the individual's taste and preferences. both forms of music involve creative processes, techniques, and styles that target different audiences. electronic music is constantly evolving, and it has a broad range of sub-genres that attract various listeners. on the other hand, beethoven's music has stood the test of time, and it is still regarded as some of the greatest classical music ever created, but it may not appeal to everyone. in conclusion, it is difficult to compare the two forms of music as they are fundamentally different, and it ultimately comes down to personal preference.
